main event: Radar detected 5 objects in Lansing, Michigan on June 6, 1964.
interesting points: The radar objects were much brighter than normal ground clutter,The objects were traveling at approximately 300 mph,There was no sound or trail observed from the objects,No clouds or searchlights were present in the area during the sighting,A local radio operator noted that the objects appeared to be moving northwest, contradicting other reports.
witness description: a radio operator and a Michigan State Police officer
